Gauteng deputy police commissioner Tommy Mthombeni says police did comprehensive work leading to the arrest of Operation Dudula leader, Nhlanhla 'Lux' Dlamini. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng deputy police commissioner Tommy Mthombeni says police did comprehensive work leading to the arrest of Operation Dudula leader, Nhlanhla 'Lux' Dlamini. Gauteng police established a task team including crime intelligence, to investigate allegations of housebreaking. READ: Nhlanhla 'Lux' to remain in custody Dlamini was arrested on Thursday night. He faces charges of housebreaking, theft and defeating the ends of justice. READ: Fears that Nhlanhla 'Lux' may be poisoned in jail Members of Operation Dudula have been protesting, demanding his release. Efforts to get Dlamini released on bail failed. Mthombeni says Dlamini is safe in police cells.